This directory contains Libgcrypt's default implementation of the
random subsystem.  When built, this subsystem will be put into a
library named `libgcrypt-random.la'.

This subsystem contains a pseudo random number generator (PRNG)
modelled after the one described in Peter Gutmann's paper: "Software
Generation of Practically Strong Random Numbers".

Files:

  core.c: core functionality.
  interface.c: public interface on top of core functionality.
  gcrypt-random-common.h: internal and public definitions.
  gcrypt-random-internal.h: internal definitions.
  gcrypt-random.h: public definitions.
  source-dev.c: Random gather module using /dev/{u,}random.
  source-egd.c: Random gather module using EGD.
  source-unix.c: Random gather module using standard Unix programs.
